Latest completed work (one-click unassigned archive)
- Added `Archive Unassigned` button in `Admin Data Tools`.
- Button archives all currently filtered unassigned markers in one action (no manual checkbox selection required).
- Keeps archive safety behavior:
  - cloud markers are soft-archived (not deleted)
  - local-only markers are archived in session state
  - `Undo Last Archive` restores the archived batch
- Updated quick-filter first chip label to `All Markers` for clarity.

Latest completed work (technical assessment QA hardening - phase 1)
- Fixed technical assessment save race between local draft autosave and cloud save:
  - Cloud save now clears any pending autosave timer before writing.
  - Prevents stale draft writes from reappearing immediately after successful cloud save.
- Hardened technical cloud save payload:
  - Uses Firestore merge writes (`setDoc(..., { merge: true })`) to avoid clobbering unrelated future metadata.
  - Adds `updatedAt` server timestamp on cloud saves.
- Hardened technical save failure behavior:
  - On cloud save failure, the current assessment is immediately persisted to local draft storage.
  - Keeps draft recovery reliable even when cloud save fails mid-session.
- Minor export hygiene:
  - Technical missing-items CSV now revokes blob URLs after download.

Latest completed work (technical assessment QA hardening - phase 2)
- Added legacy-field normalization for technical score data to improve completion tracking accuracy across older saved records.
- Completion tracking now treats common legacy aliases as equivalent to canonical fields (for example: `telecom` -> `telecomm`, `hvac` -> `mechanical`, `codesAccessibility` -> `codesAndAccessibility`).
- Unified technical progress and building-shading logic to use the same normalized scoring computation, preventing mismatches between checklist percentages and blue progress shading.
- Technical assessment panel now normalizes legacy score keys when loading/editing records, so older data opens with correct field values instead of appearing as missing.

Latest completed work (technical assessment QA hardening - phase 3 UI polish)
- Improved Technical Assessment panel clarity:
  - Added in-panel completion summary (`answered/total`, `% complete`, `sections started`).
  - Added inline warning text when one or more section starts are still missing.
  - Aligned section labels with workflow language (`Codes`, `Engineering`, `Functionality`).
  - Improved field label readability for common technical terms (for example: `Fire Alarm`, `Conveying Systems`, `Codes and Accessibility`).
- Improved Technical Progress list readability:
  - Added `Complete` status chip on fully complete buildings.
  - Added missing field count in each row summary (`x fields missing`).

