Latest completed work (blank-map runtime hotfix)
- Fixed `ReferenceError: Cannot access '<minified var>' before initialization` causing blank maps after deploy.
- Root cause was a technical-route cloud-write flag referencing `isAdminUser` before that state variable was initialized in component scope.
- Fixed by removing the early top-level reference and evaluating the cloud-write expression at render usage.

Latest completed work (AI planning scenario fit tightening)
- Tightened AI move-scenario behavior to better respect building fit and consolidation:
  - Added department-fit heuristics to avoid service/maintenance-heavy destination buildings for academic departments when viable alternatives exist.
  - Added single-building preference when the source department currently lives in one building (or when an explicit target building is requested).
  - Limited cross-building exceptions to classroom/specialized space types (for example shops/auditoria/performance/clinic/studio), instead of broad cross-building lab spillover.
- Added scenario constraints/context signals sent to AI:
  - `preferSingleBuilding`
  - `sourceHomeBuildingCount`
  - `preferAcademicFit`
  - `lowFitBuildings`
  - `crossBuildingExceptionTypes`
- Updated server-side move-scenario system prompt to explicitly enforce:
  - building-function compatibility
  - low-fit building avoidance when requested
  - single-building consolidation preference with limited exception types
- Validation:
  - `node --check ai-server/server.js` passed
  - `npm.cmd run build` passed
  - `npm.cmd run smoke` passed (`24/24 checks`)

Latest completed work (AI planning scenario fit tightening - phase 2)
- Added stricter pre-AI inventory screening for academic move scenarios:
  - Excludes low-fit/offline buildings before AI candidate generation when viable inventory remains.
  - Offline building handling currently includes Fuhr (`Hayes M. Fuhr Hall of Music`) as exclude-by-default.
- Expanded low-fit building-name heuristics for academic moves (service/maintenance, student union, residence/apartments, stadium/fitness/chapel/health-center style buildings).
- Narrowed specialized cross-building exceptions to true specialty uses (removed broad generic `special` match that was allowing too many spillover lab-like spaces).
- Added `offlineBuildings` into scenario context/constraints and reinforced server prompt instruction to treat them as exclude-by-default unless user explicitly requests them.

Latest completed work (runtime hotfix after planning-fit updates)
- Fixed frontend crash `ReferenceError: Cannot access '<minified var>' before initialization` introduced by a top-level offline-building key set using `normalizeDashboardKey` before that function was initialized.
- Resolved by switching offline-building key normalization to a local helper independent of later module symbols.
- Validation:
  - `npm.cmd run build` passed
  - `npm.cmd run smoke` passed (`24/24 checks`)

Latest completed work (AI planning strict-fit guardrails)
- Tightened strict-fit candidate auto-fill so large outlier rooms no longer blow past target SF:
  - Added strict upper-bound guard (`targetMax`) in baseline auto-fill; strict mode now refuses additions that exceed the upper fit range.
  - Added strict gap-aware room selection so fill prefers rooms closest to remaining target need instead of blindly taking largest rooms.
- Added academic-fit protection against athletics outliers for non-athletics baselines:
  - Auto-fill now excludes athletics/gym/arena/fieldhouse room types when `preferAcademicFit` is active and baseline does not include athletics types.
- Narrowed cross-building exceptions:
  - Cross-building exception matcher now allows classroom + true specialized academic spaces (shop/auditorium/performance/clinic/studio/etc.) and excludes athletics/gym/arena spillover.
  - Updated move-scenario exception label text accordingly.
- Reinforced server-side move-scenario prompt:
  - In non-athletics moves, avoid athletics/gym/arena/fieldhouse unless explicitly needed/requested.
  - In strict mode (`targetSfTolerance <= 0.05`), do not intentionally exceed upper SF bound; prefer slight under-target with explanation.
- Validation:
  - `npm.cmd run build` passed
  - `npm.cmd run smoke` passed (`24/24 checks`)

Latest completed work (scenario room halving axis alignment)
- Updated planning scenario `Halve Vertical` and `Halve Horizontal` to align with the selected room polygon orientation (room-local axes), instead of global map north/south east/west axes.
- Implementation details:
  - Halving now computes the room's dominant edge orientation.
  - Geometry is rotated into a temporary room-aligned frame, split on strict orthogonal axes there, then rotated back.
  - This keeps cuts orthogonal and visually correct on slanted/rotated floorplans.
- Validation:
  - `npm.cmd run build` passed
  - `npm.cmd run smoke` passed (`24/24 checks`)

Latest completed work (scenario halving reliability hotfix)
- Fixed bad/imbalanced room-halving outcomes on some slanted polygons after room-local alignment rollout.
- Root-cause mitigation:
  - Replaced the special-case axis splitter used by halving with the existing robust split engine (`resolveScenarioSplitPieces`) in axis-lock mode.
  - This keeps axis constraints but uses the same geometry path as manual split, improving consistency and piece validity.
- Added reliability guard:
  - If the computed best split is still highly imbalanced (>20% area imbalance), the action now aborts with a clear alert instead of creating a bad halve.
- Increased offset sampling density for halving search from 24 to 36 to better find balanced cuts.
- Validation:
  - `npm.cmd run build` passed
  - `npm.cmd run smoke` passed (`24/24 checks`)

Latest completed work (scenario halving orientation/forced-mode refinement)
- Improved room-axis detection for halving:
  - Now prioritizes dominant edge angle (wall-aligned) over weighted average orientation, then normalizes angle.
  - Reduces slant drift where split lines looked visually off-axis to room walls.
- Improved strict direction behavior:
  - `Halve Vertical` / `Halve Horizontal` no longer hard-fail due reliability threshold when orientation is explicitly forced by user.
  - Reliability guard remains for auto-orientation mode only.
- Improved equal-area search quality:
  - Added local offset refinement around best sampled split to better minimize area difference for each orientation.
- Validation:
  - `npm.cmd run build` passed
  - `npm.cmd run smoke` passed (`24/24 checks`)

Latest completed work (scenario halve button semantic fix)
- Fixed `Halve Vertical` / `Halve Horizontal` direction naming mismatch in room-local halving.
- Root cause:
  - Room-local splitter axis interpretation was correct geometrically, but mapped opposite to user-facing button names.
- Fix:
  - Added explicit orientation mapping so:
    - `Halve Vertical` produces the expected vertical divider direction in room context.
    - `Halve Horizontal` produces the expected horizontal divider direction in room context.
  - Geometry engine and equal-area search remain unchanged.
- Validation:
  - `npm.cmd run build` passed
  - `npm.cmd run smoke` passed (`24/24 checks`)
